`887b1cd2b94f9ebc709d2f7fe157c4dff21a5587` [Task 1]

## Failures and how to do differently

- Symptom: a disposable-clone cleanup step is blocked by the repo guardrail. Cause: the proof path relied on a direct
destructive SQL cleanup. Fix: use a checked-in rollback-only smoke harness instead of bypassing the guardrail [Task 1]
- Symptom: `gh pr merge` or related worktree bookkeeping fails unexpectedly. Cause: the default branch is already
checked out in another worktree such as `C:/CRX_Layer2`. Fix: verify the remote merge status before retrying local
merge actions blindly [Task 1]
- Symptom: the PR looks mostly green but the release still closes too early. Cause: the long-running GitHub main CI
job has not finished yet. Fix: keep watching the PR checks and the final GitHub Actions run until completion before
declaring the merge fully done [Task 1]

