docs\review-grain-live.md:5:2. **P1 — SECURITY DEFINER RPC bypasses 0008’s grain-read privacy** — `supabase/migrations/0012_grain_live_support.sql:15,41-43,313-321`; `supabase/migrations/0002_module1_rls.sql:25-38`; `supabase/migrations/0008_employee_privacy.sql:18-39`. `can_edit_farm` includes workers, while `can_read_private_financials` may deny them. Because the RPC is `SECURITY DEFINER`, an otherwise denied worker can call it and receive canonical marketing-plan rows, bypassing table RLS. Require `can_read_private_financials(p_farm_id)` before returning private rows—or tighten RPC authorization to roles allowed to read Grain—and add a denied-worker SQL test.
docs\review-grain-live.md:13:6. **P1 — 0008-denied users receive a dishonest empty-Grain state** — `src/data/SupabaseGrainDataGateway.ts:13-23`; `src/data/SupabaseGrainRepository.ts:41-52`; `src/GrainModule.tsx:41-46`. RLS denial normally appears as successful empty arrays, not an error. The repository does not check `can_read_private_financials`, so the UI tells a denied member to add a crop assignment instead of explaining that Grain records are private. Add an explicit permission probe and show a calm farmer-English access message before interpreting empty private tables as real emptiness.
