docs\audits\2026-07-15-sol-foundation-review\next-session-evidence\SOL-DELTA-13-RUNTIME.stderr.log:6027:The direct-table proof is structurally sensitive to each operation: a restored `INSERT` fails with the wrong RLS error, while a restored policyless `UPDATE` or `DELETE` can exit successfully with zero rows; the helper rejects both cases because it requires a nonzero exit and the exact table-permission denial. I’m now running only read-only checks: the static guard and an independent notification-link matrix against the production helper.
