docs\audits\2026-07-15-sol-foundation-review\next-session-evidence\SOL-DELTA-12B-RUNTIME.stderr.log:12927:Authenticated users retain direct `INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE` access to `push_subscriptions` from [0023_reminders.sql](C:/FarmRx/supabase/migrations/0023_reminders.sql:68), with user-only RLS policies at line 93. Migration [0041_unscoped_authenticated_write_fencing.sql](C:/FarmRx/supabase/migrations/0041_unscoped_authenticated_write_fencing.sql:141) revokes only the old RPC signatures—not direct table writes.
docs\audits\2026-07-15-sol-foundation-review\next-session-evidence\SOL-DELTA-12B-RUNTIME.stderr.log:12929:Because `push_subscriptions` has no `farm_id`, it is excluded from the epoch-trigger loop in [0040_farm_access_epoch_fencing.sql](C:/FarmRx/supabase/migrations/0040_farm_access_epoch_fencing.sql:346). An authenticated PostgREST request can therefore modify its subscription without the captured farm or access generation. RLS still prevents taking another account’s endpoint, but closure 4 is incomplete.
